{{See|Lesbian}}
==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek [[Lesbos|Lesb(os)]] + Latin(?) adjective ending [[-ian]]
===Noun===
'''lesbian'''
#A woman who is [[homosexual]]; that is, attracted to other women.

====Synonyms====
*[[dyke]] (''usually offensive, but reclaimed by many lesbians'')
*[[gay]]
*[[homosexual]]

